OL,3,CAnalysis finds 'surprising'
OL,4,Cdestinations are cheapest for a summer
OL,5,Cbreak
OL,7,FRory Boland, editor of magazine Which?
OL,8,FTravel, said: "Travelling in the
OL,9,Fsummer holidays is notoriously
OL,10,Fexpensive, and demand is again high
OL,11,Fthis year ` but our latest price
OL,12,Fanalysis shows that by being flexible
OL,13,Fon your destination, you can
OL,14,Fpotentially save hundreds of pounds.
OL,16,F"Many of the locations we found aren't
OL,17,Fthose you'd necessarily assume would
OL,18,Fbe the cheapest ` but from tiny,
OL,19,Ftraditional Greek islands to the
OL,20,Fglitzy Amalfi coast, there are
OL,21,Fbargains to be found this summer."
